idsegment and height"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <i>midsegment</i> or <i>median</i> of a trapezoid is the segment tha=
t joins the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midpoint" title=3D"Mid=
point">midpoints</a> of the legs. It is parallel to the bases. Its length <=
i>m</i> is equal to the average of the lengths of the bases <i>a</i> and <i=
>b</i> of the trapezoid,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHobbs189958_36-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trapezoid#cite_note=
-FOOTNOTEHobbs189958-36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-posamentier-bannist=
er_19-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trape=
zoid#cite_note-posamentier-bannister-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOO=
TNOTEDodge2012[httpsbooksgooglecombooksidN1b_Unptpy8CpgPA117_117]_37-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trapezoid#cite_no=
te-FOOTNOTEDodge2012[httpsbooksgooglecombooksidN1b_Unptpy8CpgPA117_117]-37"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-ringenberg_6-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trapezoid#cite_note-ringenberg-6"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e m=3D{\frac {a+b}{2}}.}">
  <semantics>
