<p>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trapezoidal_number" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Trapezoidal number">trapezoidal number</a> is a set o=
f <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Positive_integer" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Positive integer">positive integers</a> obtained by summin=
g consecutively two or more positive integers greater than one, forming a t=
rapezoidal pattern.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-57" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trapezoid#cite_note-57"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>57<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crossed_ladders_problem" =
title=3D"Crossed ladders problem">crossed ladders problem</a> is the proble=
m of finding the distance between the parallel sides of a right trapezoid, =
given the diagonal lengths and the distance from the perpendicular leg to t=
he diagonal intersection.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAlsinaNelsen2020[httpb=
ooksgooglecombooksidCGDSDwAAQBAJpgPA102_102]_58-0" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trapezoid#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAlsinaNels=
en2020[httpbooksgooglecombooksidCGDSDwAAQBAJpgPA102_102]-58"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>58<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
